 Two lawmakers in the House of Representatives, Ephraim Nwuzi from Rivers State and David Abel from Taraba State, on Wednesday defected from the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) to the All Progressives Congress (APC). The lawmakers announced their defection on the floor of the House at resumed plenary in separate letters addressed to the Speaker of the House, Femi Gbajabiamila. Read also: APC candidate, Abiru, canvasses police reforms …Says, ‘SARS must stop killing youths